{
  "texts": [
    "Grip training is emphasized as a continuous process to enhance racket control and precision.",
    "For beginners, the coach prioritizes teaching proper posture, followed by improving swing accuracy and shot execution.",
    "Maintaining the correct swing involves generating power from the rotation of the torso, along with the coordinated movement of the arm and wrist.",
    "The evaluation of shot accuracy focuses on hitting the intended target or clearing the net correctly.",
    "In terms of step, the coach emphasizes positioning the dominant foot underneath the shuttlecock's expected landing spot and highlights the importance of the split step for quick post-shot preparation."
  ]
}